{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"My work is play."},{"time":2000,"text":"And I play when I design."},{"time":4000,"text":"I even looked it up in the dictionary, to make sure"},{"time":6000,"text":"that I actually do that,"},{"time":8000,"text":"and the definition of play,"},{"time":10000,"text":"number one, was engaging in a childlike"},{"time":12000,"text":"activity or endeavor,"},{"time":14000,"text":"and number two was gambling."},{"time":17000,"text":"And I realize I do both"},{"time":19000,"text":"when I'm designing."},{"time":21000,"text":"I'm both a kid and I'm gambling all the time."},{"time":24000,"text":"And I think that if you're not,"},{"time":26000,"text":"there's probably something inherently wrong"},{"time":28000,"text":"with the structure or the situation you're in,"},{"time":30000,"text":"if you're a designer."},{"time":32000,"text":"But the serious part is what threw me,"},{"time":34000,"text":"and I couldn't quite get a handle"},{"time":38000,"text":"on it until I remembered an essay."},{"time":41000,"text":"And it's an essay I read 30 years ago."},{"time":44000,"text":"It was written by Russell Baker,"},{"time":46000,"text":"who used to write an \"Observer\" column in the New York Times."},{"time":49000,"text":"He's a wonderful humorist. And I'm going to read you"},{"time":51000,"text":"this essay,"},{"time":53000,"text":"or an excerpt from it"},{"time":55000,"text":"because it really hit home for me."},{"time":58000,"text":"Here is a letter of friendly advice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":61000,"text":"Be serious, it says."},{"time":63000,"text":"What it means, of course, is, be solemn."},{"time":66000,"text":"Being solemn is easy."},{"time":68000,"text":"Being serious is hard."},{"time":71000,"text":"Children almost always begin by being serious,"},{"time":73000,"text":"which is what makes them so entertaining"},{"time":75000,"text":"when compared with adults as a class."},{"time":78000,"text":"Adults, on the whole, are solemn."},{"time":80000,"text":"In politics, the rare candidate who is serious,"},{"time":83000,"text":"like Adlai Stevenson,"},{"time":85000,"text":"is easily overwhelmed by one who is solemn, like Eisenhower."},{"time":88000,"text":"That's because it is hard for most people"},{"time":90000,"text":"to recognize seriousness, which is rare,"},{"time":93000,"text":"but more comfortable to endorse solemnity,"},{"time":95000,"text":"which is commonplace."},{"time":98000,"text":"Jogging, which is commonplace,"},{"time":100000,"text":"and widely accepted as good for you, is solemn."},{"time":103000,"text":"Poker is serious."},{"time":105000,"text":"Washington, D.C. is solemn."},{"time":108000,"text":"New York is serious."},{"time":110000,"text":"Going to educational conferences to tell you anything"},{"time":112000,"text":"about the future is solemn."},{"time":115000,"text":"Taking a long walk by yourself,"},{"time":117000,"text":"during which you devise a foolproof scheme for robbing Tiffany's,"},{"time":120000,"text":"is serious."}]},{"cues":[{"time":122000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":123000,"text":"Now, when I apply Russell Baker's definition"},{"time":125000,"text":"of solemnity or seriousness to design,"},{"time":127000,"text":"it doesn't necessarily make any particular point about quality."},{"time":130000,"text":"Solemn design is often important and very effective design."},{"time":133000,"text":"Solemn design is also socially correct,"},{"time":136000,"text":"and is accepted by appropriate audiences."},{"time":138000,"text":"It's what right-thinking designers"},{"time":141000,"text":"and all the clients are striving for."},{"time":143000,"text":"Serious design, serious play,"},{"time":145000,"text":"is something else."},{"time":147000,"text":"For one thing, it often happens"},{"time":149000,"text":"spontaneously, intuitively,"},{"time":152000,"text":"accidentally or incidentally."},{"time":154000,"text":"It can be achieved out of innocence, or arrogance,"},{"time":156000,"text":"or out of selfishness, sometimes out of carelessness."},{"time":159000,"text":"But mostly, it's achieved through all those kind of crazy"},{"time":163000,"text":"parts of human behavior that"},{"time":165000,"text":"don't really make any sense."}]},{"cues":[{"time":167000,"text":"Serious design is imperfect."},{"time":169000,"text":"It's filled with the kind of craft laws that come from something being"},{"time":171000,"text":"the first of its kind."},{"time":173000,"text":"Serious design is also -- often -- quite unsuccessful"},{"time":176000,"text":"from the solemn point of view."},{"time":178000,"text":"That's because the art of serious play"},{"time":180000,"text":"is about invention, change, rebellion -- not perfection."},{"time":183000,"text":"Perfection happens during solemn play."},{"time":187000,"text":"Now, I always saw design careers"},{"time":189000,"text":"like surreal staircases."},{"time":192000,"text":"If you look at the staircase, you'll see"},{"time":195000,"text":"that in your 20s the risers are very high"},{"time":198000,"text":"and the steps are very short,"},{"time":201000,"text":"and you make huge discoveries."},{"time":203000,"text":"You sort of leap up very quickly in your youth."},{"time":206000,"text":"That's because you don't know anything and you have a lot to learn,"},{"time":208000,"text":"and so that anything you do is a learning experience"},{"time":211000,"text":"and you're just jumping right up there."},{"time":213000,"text":"As you get older, the risers get shallower"},{"time":215000,"text":"and the steps get wider,"},{"time":217000,"text":"and you start moving along at a slower pace"},{"time":220000,"text":"because you're making fewer discoveries."},{"time":222000,"text":"And as you get older and more decrepit,"},{"time":224000,"text":"you sort of inch along on this"},{"time":226000,"text":"sort of depressing, long staircase,"},{"time":228000,"text":"leading you into oblivion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":230000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":232000,"text":"I find it's actually getting really hard to be serious."},{"time":237000,"text":"I'm hired to be solemn, but I find more and more"},{"time":240000,"text":"that I'm solemn when I don't have to be."},{"time":242000,"text":"And in my 35 years of working experience,"},{"time":245000,"text":"I think I was really serious four times."},{"time":248000,"text":"And I'm going to show them to you now,"},{"time":250000,"text":"because they came out of very specific conditions."},{"time":253000,"text":"It's great to be a kid."},{"time":255000,"text":"Now, when I was in my early 20s,"},{"time":258000,"text":"I worked in the record business, designing record covers for CBS Records,"},{"time":261000,"text":"and I had no idea what a great job I had."},{"time":263000,"text":"I thought everybody had a job like that."},{"time":266000,"text":"And what --"},{"time":268000,"text":"the way I looked at design and the way I looked at the world was,"},{"time":271000,"text":"what was going on around me"},{"time":273000,"text":"and the things that came at the time I walked into design"},{"time":275000,"text":"were the enemy."},{"time":277000,"text":"I really, really, really hated"},{"time":279000,"text":"the typeface Helvetica."},{"time":281000,"text":"I thought the typeface Helvetica"},{"time":284000,"text":"was the cleanest, most boring, most fascistic,"},{"time":287000,"text":"really repressive typeface,"},{"time":290000,"text":"and I hated everything that was designed in Helvetica."},{"time":292000,"text":"And when I was in"},{"time":294000,"text":"my college days,"},{"time":296000,"text":"this was the sort of design"},{"time":298000,"text":"that was fashionable and popular."},{"time":300000,"text":"This is actually quite a lovely book jacket by Rudy de Harak,"},{"time":303000,"text":"but I just hated it, because it was designed with Helvetica,"},{"time":306000,"text":"and I made parodies about it."},{"time":308000,"text":"I just thought it was, you know, completely boring."}]},{"cues":[{"time":311000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":313000,"text":"So -- so, my goal in life"},{"time":315000,"text":"was to do stuff that wasn't made out of Helvetica."},{"time":319000,"text":"And to do stuff that wasn't made out of Helvetica"},{"time":321000,"text":"was actually kind of hard because you had to find it."},{"time":324000,"text":"And there weren't a lot of books about the history of design"},{"time":327000,"text":"in the early 70s. There weren't --"},{"time":329000,"text":"there wasn't a plethora of design publishing."},{"time":331000,"text":"You actually had to go to antique stores. You had to go to Europe."},{"time":333000,"text":"You had to go places and find the stuff."},{"time":336000,"text":"And what I responded to was, you know,"},{"time":338000,"text":"Art Nouveau, or deco,"},{"time":341000,"text":"or Victorian typography,"},{"time":343000,"text":"or things that were just completely not Helvetica."},{"time":347000,"text":"And I taught myself design this way,"},{"time":350000,"text":"and this was sort of my early years,"},{"time":352000,"text":"and I used these things"},{"time":354000,"text":"in really goofy ways"},{"time":356000,"text":"on record covers and in my design."},{"time":358000,"text":"I wasn't educated. I just sort of"},{"time":360000,"text":"put these things together."},{"time":362000,"text":"I mixed up Victorian designs with pop,"},{"time":364000,"text":"and I mixed up Art Nouveau with something else."},{"time":367000,"text":"And I made these very lush,"},{"time":369000,"text":"very elaborate record covers,"},{"time":372000,"text":"not because I was being a post-modernist or a historicist --"},{"time":375000,"text":"because I didn't know what those things were."},{"time":377000,"text":"I just hated Helvetica."}]},{"cues":[{"time":379000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":380000,"text":"And that kind of passion"},{"time":383000,"text":"drove me into very serious play,"},{"time":385000,"text":"a kind of play I could never do now"},{"time":388000,"text":"because I'm too well-educated."},{"time":390000,"text":"And there's something wonderful about"},{"time":393000,"text":"that form of youth,"},{"time":395000,"text":"where you can let yourself"},{"time":398000,"text":"grow and play, and be"},{"time":400000,"text":"really a brat, and then accomplish things."},{"time":403000,"text":"By the end of the '70s, actually,"},{"time":405000,"text":"the stuff became known."},{"time":407000,"text":"I mean, these covers appeared all over the world,"},{"time":409000,"text":"and they started winning awards,"},{"time":411000,"text":"and people knew them."},{"time":413000,"text":"And I was suddenly a post-modernist,"},{"time":416000,"text":"and I began a career as -- in my own business."},{"time":419000,"text":"And first I was praised for it, then criticized for it,"},{"time":422000,"text":"but the fact of the matter was, I had become solemn."},{"time":425000,"text":"I didn't do what I think"},{"time":427000,"text":"was a piece of serious work again for about 14 years."},{"time":431000,"text":"I spent most of the '80s being quite solemn,"},{"time":433000,"text":"turning out these sorts of designs"},{"time":435000,"text":"that I was expected to do"},{"time":437000,"text":"because that's who I was,"},{"time":439000,"text":"and I was living in this cycle of going from serious to solemn"},{"time":442000,"text":"to hackneyed to dead, and getting rediscovered all over again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":447000,"text":"So, here was the second condition"},{"time":449000,"text":"for which I think I accomplished some serious play."},{"time":454000,"text":"There's a Paul Newman movie"},{"time":456000,"text":"that I love called \"The Verdict.\""},{"time":458000,"text":"I don't know how many of you have seen it, but it's a beaut."},{"time":461000,"text":"And in the movie, he plays"},{"time":463000,"text":"a down-and-out lawyer"},{"time":465000,"text":"who's become an ambulance chaser."},{"time":467000,"text":"And he's taken on --"},{"time":469000,"text":"he's given, actually -- a malpractice suit to handle"},{"time":472000,"text":"that's sort of an easy deal,"},{"time":474000,"text":"and in the midst of trying to connect the deal,"},{"time":476000,"text":"he starts to empathize"},{"time":478000,"text":"and identify with his client,"},{"time":480000,"text":"and he regains his morality and purpose,"},{"time":483000,"text":"and he goes on to win the case."},{"time":485000,"text":"And in the depth of despair,"},{"time":488000,"text":"in the midst of the movie, when it looks like he can't pull this thing off,"},{"time":492000,"text":"and he needs this case,"},{"time":494000,"text":"he needs to win this case so badly."},{"time":496000,"text":"There's a shot of Paul Newman alone,"},{"time":499000,"text":"in his office, saying,"},{"time":502000,"text":"\"This is the case. There are no other cases."},{"time":505000,"text":"This is the case. There are no other cases.\""},{"time":508000,"text":"And in that moment of"},{"time":510000,"text":"desire and focus,"},{"time":512000,"text":"he can win."},{"time":514000,"text":"And that is a wonderful"},{"time":516000,"text":"position to be in to create some serious play."},{"time":520000,"text":"And I had that moment in 1994"},{"time":523000,"text":"when I met a theater director"},{"time":525000,"text":"named George Wolfe,"},{"time":527000,"text":"who was going to have me design"},{"time":529000,"text":"an identity for the New York Shakespeare Festival,"},{"time":532000,"text":"then known,"},{"time":534000,"text":"and then became the Public Theater."},{"time":536000,"text":"And I began getting immersed"},{"time":538000,"text":"in this project"},{"time":540000,"text":"in a way I never was before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":542000,"text":"This is what theater advertising looked like at that time."},{"time":545000,"text":"This is what was in the newspapers and in the New York Times."},{"time":548000,"text":"So, this is sort of a comment on the time."},{"time":551000,"text":"And the Public Theater actually had much better advertising than this."},{"time":554000,"text":"They had no logo and no identity,"},{"time":556000,"text":"but they had these very iconic posters"},{"time":559000,"text":"painted by Paul Davis."},{"time":561000,"text":"And George Wolf had taken over from another director"},{"time":564000,"text":"and he wanted to change the theater,"},{"time":566000,"text":"and he wanted to make it urban and loud"},{"time":568000,"text":"and a place that was inclusive."},{"time":571000,"text":"So, drawing on my love of typography,"},{"time":574000,"text":"I immersed myself into this project."},{"time":577000,"text":"And what was different about it was the totality of it,"},{"time":581000,"text":"was that I really became the voice, the visual voice, of a place"},{"time":585000,"text":"in a way I had never done before,"},{"time":587000,"text":"where every aspect --"},{"time":589000,"text":"the smallest ad, the ticket, whatever it was --"},{"time":591000,"text":"was designed by me."},{"time":593000,"text":"There was no format."},{"time":595000,"text":"There was no in-house department that these things were pushed to."},{"time":598000,"text":"I literally for three years made everything --"},{"time":600000,"text":"every scrap of paper, everything online,"},{"time":603000,"text":"that this theater did."},{"time":605000,"text":"And it was the only job,"},{"time":607000,"text":"even though I was doing other jobs."},{"time":609000,"text":"I lived and breathed it in a way I haven't"},{"time":611000,"text":"with a client since."},{"time":613000,"text":"It enabled me to really express myself and grow."},{"time":617000,"text":"And I think that you know"},{"time":619000,"text":"when you're going to be given this position,"},{"time":621000,"text":"and it's rare, but when you get it and you have this opportunity,"},{"time":625000,"text":"it's the moment of serious play."}]},{"cues":[{"time":627000,"text":"I did these things, and I still do them."},{"time":630000,"text":"I still work for the Public Theater."},{"time":632000,"text":"I'm on their board, and"},{"time":634000,"text":"I still am involved with it."},{"time":637000,"text":"The high point of the Public Theater, I think, was in 1996,"},{"time":640000,"text":"two years after I designed it,"},{"time":642000,"text":"which was the \"Bring in 'da Noise, Bring in 'da Funk\" campaign"},{"time":645000,"text":"that was all over New York."},{"time":647000,"text":"But something happened to it, and what happened to it was,"},{"time":650000,"text":"it became very popular."},{"time":652000,"text":"And that is a kiss of death for something serious"},{"time":655000,"text":"because it makes it solemn."},{"time":658000,"text":"And what happened was"},{"time":660000,"text":"that New York City, to a degree,"},{"time":662000,"text":"ate my identity"},{"time":665000,"text":"because people began to copy it."},{"time":668000,"text":"Here's an ad in the New York Times"},{"time":670000,"text":"somebody did for a play called \"Mind Games.\""},{"time":674000,"text":"Then \"Chicago\" came out, used similar graphics,"},{"time":677000,"text":"and the Public Theater's identity was just totally eaten and taken away,"},{"time":680000,"text":"which meant I had to change it."},{"time":683000,"text":"So, I changed it so that every season was different,"},{"time":686000,"text":"and I continued to do these posters,"},{"time":688000,"text":"but they never had the seriousness"},{"time":690000,"text":"of the first identity"},{"time":692000,"text":"because they were too individual, and they didn't have that heft"},{"time":695000,"text":"of everything being the same thing."},{"time":698000,"text":"Now -- and I think since the Public Theater,"},{"time":701000,"text":"I must have done more than a dozen"},{"time":703000,"text":"cultural identities for major institutions,"},{"time":706000,"text":"and I don't think I ever -- I ever"},{"time":708000,"text":"grasped that seriousness again --"},{"time":710000,"text":"I do them for very big, important institutions"},{"time":712000,"text":"in New York City."}]},{"cues":[{"time":714000,"text":"The institutions are solemn,"},{"time":717000,"text":"and so is the design."},{"time":719000,"text":"They're better crafted than the Public Theater was,"},{"time":721000,"text":"and they spend more money on them, but I think"},{"time":723000,"text":"that that moment comes and goes."},{"time":726000,"text":"The best way to accomplish serious design --"},{"time":728000,"text":"which I think we all have the opportunity to do --"},{"time":731000,"text":"is to be totally and completely unqualified for the job."},{"time":735000,"text":"That doesn't happen very often,"},{"time":737000,"text":"but it happened to me in the year 2000,"},{"time":739000,"text":"when for some reason or another,"},{"time":741000,"text":"a whole pile of different architects"},{"time":743000,"text":"started to ask me to design"},{"time":745000,"text":"the insides of theaters with them,"},{"time":747000,"text":"where I would take environmental graphics and work them into buildings."},{"time":750000,"text":"I'd never done this kind of work before."},{"time":752000,"text":"I didn't know how to read an architectural plan,"},{"time":755000,"text":"I didn't know what they were talking about,"},{"time":757000,"text":"and I really couldn't handle the fact that a job --"},{"time":759000,"text":"a single job -- could go on for four years"},{"time":761000,"text":"because I was used to immediacy in graphic design,"},{"time":764000,"text":"and that kind of attention to detail"},{"time":766000,"text":"was really bad for somebody like me, with ADD."}]},{"cues":[{"time":769000,"text":"So, it was a rough -- it was a rough go,"},{"time":772000,"text":"but I fell in love with this process"},{"time":775000,"text":"of actually integrating graphics into architecture"},{"time":778000,"text":"because I didn't know what I was doing."},{"time":781000,"text":"I said, \"Why can't the signage be on the floor?\""},{"time":783000,"text":"New Yorkers look at their feet."},{"time":785000,"text":"And then I found that actors and actresses"},{"time":787000,"text":"actually take their cues from the floor,"},{"time":789000,"text":"so it turned out that these sorts of sign systems"},{"time":792000,"text":"began to make sense."},{"time":794000,"text":"They integrated with the building in really peculiar ways."},{"time":797000,"text":"They ran around corners,"},{"time":799000,"text":"they went up sides of buildings,"},{"time":802000,"text":"and they melded into the architecture."},{"time":804000,"text":"This is Symphony Space on 90th Street and Broadway,"},{"time":807000,"text":"and the type is interwoven into the stainless steel"},{"time":810000,"text":"and backlit with fiber optics."},{"time":814000,"text":"And the architect, Jim Polshek,"},{"time":816000,"text":"essentially gave me a canvas"},{"time":818000,"text":"to play typography out on."},{"time":820000,"text":"And it was serious play."},{"time":822000,"text":"This is the children's museum in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania,"},{"time":825000,"text":"made out of completely inexpensive materials."},{"time":828000,"text":"Extruded typography that's backlit with neon."},{"time":831000,"text":"Things I never did before, built before."},{"time":833000,"text":"I just thought they'd be kind of fun to do."},{"time":835000,"text":"Donors' walls made out of Lucite."},{"time":838000,"text":"And then, inexpensive signage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":841000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":847000,"text":"I think my favorite of these"},{"time":849000,"text":"was this little job in Newark, New Jersey."},{"time":851000,"text":"It's a performing arts school."},{"time":854000,"text":"This is the building that -- they had no money,"},{"time":857000,"text":"and they had to recast it, and they said,"},{"time":859000,"text":"if we give you 100,000 dollars, what can you do with it?"},{"time":862000,"text":"And I did a little Photoshop job on it, and I said,"},{"time":864000,"text":"Well, I think we can paint it."},{"time":866000,"text":"And we did. And it was play."},{"time":870000,"text":"And there's the building. Everything was painted --"},{"time":873000,"text":"typography over the whole damn thing,"},{"time":875000,"text":"including the air conditioning ducts."},{"time":877000,"text":"I hired guys who paint flats"},{"time":879000,"text":"fixed on the sides of garages"},{"time":882000,"text":"to do the painting on the building, and they loved it."},{"time":884000,"text":"They got into it -- they took the job incredibly seriously."},{"time":886000,"text":"They used to climb up on the building and call me"},{"time":888000,"text":"and tell me that they had to correct my typography --"},{"time":891000,"text":"that my spacing was wrong, and they moved it,"},{"time":893000,"text":"and they did wonderful things with it."},{"time":895000,"text":"They were pretty serious, too. It was quite wonderful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":898000,"text":"By the time I did Bloomberg's headquarters"},{"time":901000,"text":"my work had begun to become accepted."},{"time":905000,"text":"People wanted it in big, expensive places."},{"time":908000,"text":"And that began to make it solemn."},{"time":910000,"text":"Bloomberg was all about numbers,"},{"time":912000,"text":"and we did big numbers through the space"},{"time":915000,"text":"and the numbers were projected on a spectacular LED"},{"time":918000,"text":"that my partner, Lisa Strausfeld, programmed."},{"time":921000,"text":"But it became the end"},{"time":923000,"text":"of the seriousness of the play,"},{"time":926000,"text":"and it started to, once again, become solemn."},{"time":929000,"text":"This is a current project"},{"time":931000,"text":"in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania,"},{"time":933000,"text":"where I got to be goofy."},{"time":935000,"text":"I was invited to design"},{"time":937000,"text":"a logo for this neighborhood, called the North Side,"},{"time":940000,"text":"and I thought it was silly for a neighborhood to have a logo."},{"time":943000,"text":"I think that's rather creepy, actually. Why would a neighborhood have a logo?"},{"time":946000,"text":"A neighborhood has a thing -- it's got a landmark, it's got a place,"},{"time":948000,"text":"it's got a restaurant. It doesn't have a logo. I mean, what would that be?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":951000,"text":"So I had to actually give a presentation"},{"time":954000,"text":"to a city council"},{"time":956000,"text":"and neighborhood constituents,"},{"time":958000,"text":"and I went to Pittsburgh and I said,"},{"time":961000,"text":"\"You know, really what you have here"},{"time":963000,"text":"are all these underpasses"},{"time":965000,"text":"that separate the neighborhood from the center of town."},{"time":968000,"text":"Why don't you celebrate them, and make the underpasses landmarks?\""},{"time":971000,"text":"So I began doing this crazy presentation"},{"time":974000,"text":"of these installations --"},{"time":976000,"text":"potential installations -- on"},{"time":979000,"text":"these underpass bridges,"},{"time":981000,"text":"and stood up in front of the city council --"},{"time":983000,"text":"and was a little bit scared,"},{"time":985000,"text":"I have to admit."},{"time":987000,"text":"But I was so utterly unqualified for this project,"},{"time":991000,"text":"and so utterly ridiculous,"},{"time":993000,"text":"and ignored the brief so desperately"},{"time":997000,"text":"that I think they just embraced it with wholeheartedness,"},{"time":1000000,"text":"just completely because it was so goofy to begin with."},{"time":1004000,"text":"And this is the bridge they're actually"},{"time":1006000,"text":"painting up and preparing as we speak."},{"time":1009000,"text":"It will change every six months, and it will become an art installation"},{"time":1012000,"text":"in the North Side of Pittsburgh,"},{"time":1014000,"text":"and it will probably become a landmark in the area."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1017000,"text":"John Hockenberry told you a bit about"},{"time":1020000,"text":"my travail with Citibank,"},{"time":1022000,"text":"that is now a 10-year relationship, and I still work with them."},{"time":1026000,"text":"And I actually am amused by them and like them,"},{"time":1029000,"text":"and think that as a very, very, very, very, very big corporation"},{"time":1032000,"text":"they actually keep their graphics very nice."},{"time":1035000,"text":"I drew the logo for Citibank"},{"time":1037000,"text":"on a napkin in the first meeting."},{"time":1040000,"text":"That was the play part of the job."},{"time":1042000,"text":"And then I spent a year"},{"time":1044000,"text":"going to long, tedious,"},{"time":1046000,"text":"boring meetings,"},{"time":1048000,"text":"trying to sell this logo through"},{"time":1050000,"text":"to a huge corporation"},{"time":1052000,"text":"to the point of tears."},{"time":1054000,"text":"I thought I was going to go crazy at the end of this year."},{"time":1056000,"text":"We made idiotic presentations"},{"time":1058000,"text":"showing how the Citi logo made sense,"},{"time":1060000,"text":"and how it was really derived from an umbrella,"},{"time":1062000,"text":"and we made animations of these things,"},{"time":1064000,"text":"and we came back and forth and back and forth and back and forth."},{"time":1067000,"text":"And it was worth it, because they bought this thing,"},{"time":1070000,"text":"and it played out on such a grand scale,"},{"time":1072000,"text":"and it's so internationally recognizable,"},{"time":1076000,"text":"but for me it was actually a very, very depressing year."},{"time":1080000,"text":"As a matter of fact, they actually never bought onto the logo"},{"time":1082000,"text":"until Fallon put it on"},{"time":1084000,"text":"its very good \"Live Richly\" campaign,"},{"time":1086000,"text":"and then everybody accepted it all over the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1090000,"text":"So during this time I needed"},{"time":1092000,"text":"some kind of counterbalance"},{"time":1094000,"text":"for this crazy, crazy existence"},{"time":1096000,"text":"of going to these long, idiotic meetings."},{"time":1098000,"text":"And I was up in my country house,"},{"time":1100000,"text":"and for some reason, I began painting"},{"time":1102000,"text":"these very big, very involved,"},{"time":1105000,"text":"laborious, complicated"},{"time":1108000,"text":"maps of the entire world,"},{"time":1110000,"text":"and listing every place on the planet, and putting them in,"},{"time":1113000,"text":"and misspelling them, and putting things in the wrong spot,"},{"time":1115000,"text":"and completely controlling the information,"},{"time":1117000,"text":"and going totally and completely nuts with it."},{"time":1120000,"text":"They would take me about six months initially,"},{"time":1123000,"text":"but then I started getting faster at it."},{"time":1125000,"text":"Here's the United States."},{"time":1127000,"text":"Every single city of the United States is on here."},{"time":1129000,"text":"And it hung for about eight months"},{"time":1131000,"text":"at the Cooper-Hewitt, and people walked up to it,"},{"time":1134000,"text":"and they would point to a part of the map"},{"time":1136000,"text":"and they'd say, \"Oh, I've been here.\""},{"time":1138000,"text":"And, of course, they couldn't have been because it's in the wrong spot."},{"time":1141000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1142000,"text":"But what I liked about it was,"},{"time":1144000,"text":"I was controlling my own idiotic information,"},{"time":1147000,"text":"and I was creating my own palette of information,"},{"time":1150000,"text":"and I was totally and completely"},{"time":1152000,"text":"at play."},{"time":1154000,"text":"One of my favorites was"},{"time":1156000,"text":"this painting I did of Florida after the 2000 election"},{"time":1159000,"text":"that has the election results rolling around in the water."},{"time":1163000,"text":"I keep that for evidence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1165000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1166000,"text":"Somebody"},{"time":1168000,"text":"was up at my house and saw the paintings"},{"time":1170000,"text":"and recommended them to a gallery,"},{"time":1172000,"text":"and I had a first show"},{"time":1174000,"text":"about two-and-a-half years ago, and I showed these paintings"},{"time":1177000,"text":"that I'm showing you now."},{"time":1180000,"text":"And then a funny thing happened -- they sold."},{"time":1183000,"text":"And they sold quickly,"},{"time":1186000,"text":"and became rather popular."},{"time":1189000,"text":"We started making prints from them."},{"time":1191000,"text":"This is Manhattan, one from the series."},{"time":1195000,"text":"This is a print from the United States which we did in red, white and blue."},{"time":1198000,"text":"We began doing these big silkscreen prints,"},{"time":1201000,"text":"and they started selling, too."},{"time":1203000,"text":"So, the gallery wanted me to have another show"},{"time":1205000,"text":"in two years,"},{"time":1207000,"text":"which meant that I really"},{"time":1210000,"text":"had to paint these paintings"},{"time":1212000,"text":"much faster"},{"time":1214000,"text":"than I had ever done them. And I --"},{"time":1216000,"text":"they started to become more political, and I picked areas"},{"time":1219000,"text":"that sort of were in the news"},{"time":1221000,"text":"or that I had some feeling about,"},{"time":1223000,"text":"and I began doing these things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1225000,"text":"And then this funny thing happened."},{"time":1227000,"text":"I found that I was no longer at play."},{"time":1230000,"text":"I was actually in this solemn landscape"},{"time":1233000,"text":"of fulfilling an expectation"},{"time":1235000,"text":"for a show,"},{"time":1237000,"text":"which is not where I started with these things."},{"time":1239000,"text":"So, while they became successful,"},{"time":1242000,"text":"I know how to make them,"},{"time":1244000,"text":"so I'm not a neophyte,"},{"time":1246000,"text":"and they're no longer serious --"},{"time":1248000,"text":"they have become solemn."},{"time":1251000,"text":"And that's a terrifying factor --"},{"time":1254000,"text":"when you start something and it turns that way --"},{"time":1256000,"text":"because it means that all that's left for you"},{"time":1259000,"text":"is to go back and to find out"},{"time":1261000,"text":"what the next thing is that you can push,"},{"time":1264000,"text":"that you can invent, that you can be ignorant about,"},{"time":1267000,"text":"that you can be arrogant about,"},{"time":1269000,"text":"that you can fail with,"},{"time":1271000,"text":"and that you can be a fool with."},{"time":1273000,"text":"Because in the end, that's how you grow,"},{"time":1276000,"text":"and that's all that matters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1278000,"text":"So, I'm plugging along here --"},{"time":1280000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1283000,"text":"and I'm just going to have to blow up the staircase."},{"time":1285000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]}]}